KCB Group has been named the 2017 Bank of the Year—Kenya, during the 18th Banker Awards held in London on Thursday.
 KCB Group was honoured for its sustainable growth and efforts in ensuring financial inclusion for all. 
 ALSO READ:

Sh50 million theft brothers scored As in high school

 The Banker Awards are aimed at recognising top banks across the globe not only based on their all year round financial performance but also based on their multi-channel banking strategies and efforts in driving financial inclusion.
 The awards are organised by The Banker - a UK based economic and financial intelligence publication.




